Every been in the mood for some good tacos or burrito and wanted to try something new... if so don’t think about this place, go to your regular spot. This post is straight from the stomach and wallet so it won’t be nice.  I just picked up a deflated small burrito, with a side of decent beans and rice and WATERY sauce, I won’t even call it salsa.  There’s more lettuce than meat which doesn’t make sense for what you pay.  Speaking of which, don’t trust the online pictures of the menu. My price in store was significantly higher and when questioned why the difference the response “we do not have a menu online”.  There’s a point of responsibility you should take when you know something online about your business is different than what you offer, price is one of them. So since you do not have an online presence but know the one out there represents your establishment allow me to help other stay away from here. Over $30 for two people to eat takeout tacos and a lettuce burrito... no thanks. Decent taste but better options nearby.

Mary's Taqueria serves my favorite tacos in Chicago! Ordered the pastor taco dinner to go, and was totally blown away. The flavor of the marinade combined with the aroma from the fat is just simply superb. SOOO GOOD. Even the bean that came with the dinner was so tasty. I never thought that I would comment on a side dish tbh but it's just so much better than everyone else. Fast and friendly service + great food. So glad that Mary's is right in the neighborhood. Would recommend to anyone who's looking for no frills good tacos.

Great little taco restaurant right off the 18th street expressway exit. The restaurant itself is cute, lots of seating, and even has a little bodega in the very back. It reminds me of the little neighborhood restaurants back in Mexico. I ordered their taco dinner for $9 and was very happy: 3 tacos, rice, and beans. Very flavorful steak and pork tacos. Their chips and guacamole are also decently priced for how much guacamole they actually give you (A LOT).
